# Project Proposal

## Project Title

Sentiment Analysis of Airline Reviews Using Deep Learning


## Problem Statement
The goal of this project is to classify airline-related tweets into positive, neutral, or negative sentiment categories using deep learning techniques.
This problem is important because sentiment analysis helps companies understand customer opinions and improve service quality.
The model will predict the sentiment label of a tweet.


## Dataset

Dataset Name:
Twitter US Airline Sentiment Dataset
Dataset Source:
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/crowdflower/twitter-airline-sentiment

Dataset Description:

* Approximately 14,000 tweets
* Input: tweet text
* Output labels:

  * positive
  * neutral
  * negative
* Format: CSV



## Planned Method

### Baseline Model

TF-IDF + Logistic Regression

### Deep Learning Model

LSTM Neural Network

### Loss Function

CrossEntropyLoss

### Evaluation Metrics

* Accuracy
* Precision
* Recall
* F1-score

### Data Split

* Train: 70%
* Validation: 15%
* Test: 15%
## Expected Challenges
Possible challenges include:
noisy tweet text,
class imbalance,
overfitting,
preprocessing hashtags and emojis,
limited computational resources.

